When `interleave` is called, that will always be already a copy, so it would be nice to avoid a second copy there as well

Maybe the above if/else can be reorganized slightly, like:

```
if self._is_single_block or not self.is_mixed_type:
  if self.blocks[0].is_datetimetz:
    ...
  elif self.blocks[0].is_extension:
    ...
  else:
    ....
  if copy or na_value is not lib.no_default:
    arr = arr.copy()
else:
  arr = self._interleave(dtype=dtype, na_value=na_value)
